        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "A large design decision is how should we handle numbers in our `Value` enum? This issue is to list options and collect opinions on the best method.\n## Prior Work\n- [JSON specification.](http://ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST/ECMA-404.pdf)\n- [Why does `serde_json` use 3 types of number?](https://github.com/serde-rs/json/issues/48)\n- [`serde_json`'s JSON type.](https://serde-rs.github.io/json/serde_json/value/enum.Value.html)\n- [`rustc-serialize's` JSON type.](https://doc.rust-lang.org/rustc-serialize/rustc_serialize/json/index.html)\n## Options\n- [Option 1: Single type](#issuecomment-198755355)\n- [Option 2: Exact types](#issuecomment-198755432)\n- [Option 3: Abstracted types](#issuecomment-198755518)\n- [Option 4: Another enum](#issuecomment-204611783)\n"
